WEBVTT

00:17.040 --> 00:18.600
How much longer will it take?

00:18.960 --> 00:20.240
What's up with Zee?

00:21.160 --> 00:22.520
- Sir...
- What happened?

00:22.920 --> 00:25.040
You should give this to J.R.D.

00:26.240 --> 00:27.520
Are you nervous?

00:27.680 --> 00:28.640
Fine, I'll give it to him.

00:28.720 --> 00:30.440
Sir, what about Mr. Gopalan?

00:30.960 --> 00:33.000
- Yes, Mr. Gopalan,
you must do this. - What, me?

00:33.200 --> 00:34.000
Why should I?

00:34.000 --> 00:35.480
- Finally, he's here.
- Good morning!

00:35.600 --> 00:36.520
- Good morning.
- Good morning!

00:36.800 --> 00:37.720
Morning, Mr. Desai.

00:37.760 --> 00:40.600
I think you should give
this bouquet to J.R.D.

00:40.760 --> 00:43.080
The idea of watchmaking
was yours, wasn't it?

00:43.640 --> 00:45.320
Are you meeting
J.R.D. for the first time?

00:45.880 --> 00:46.760
That is right.

00:47.000 --> 00:48.280
In that case, you should give it.

00:48.560 --> 00:50.720
Come on!
Breakfast is getting cold. Come on.

00:51.040 --> 00:52.280
- Come on. Come on, guys.
- We're running late. Let's go.

00:52.280 --> 00:54.280
- Let's go. - Let's not keep him
waiting for breakfast.

00:54.320 --> 00:55.600
- I... I don't think...
- Breakfast...

00:55.800 --> 00:57.240
What...

01:04.080 --> 01:06.840
Is this what you've manufactured
after all these years of hard work?

01:12.880 --> 01:14.800
I'd appreciate some answers, please.

01:14.880 --> 01:16.720
I'm extremely sorry, Jeh.

01:17.680 --> 01:19.360
We will fix it.
Please give us some time.

01:19.400 --> 01:20.560
How much time do you need?

01:22.560 --> 01:24.480
You wanted a challenge.

01:25.440 --> 01:27.200
Yet this is how you rise to it.

01:29.040 --> 01:32.080
Time is ticking,
yet your watch can't keep up.

01:33.400 --> 01:36.360
Sir, we had performed
all the tests on the watch.

01:36.360 --> 01:40.000
We can't say that to our customers,
Mr. Gopalan.

01:48.840 --> 01:49.760
Anyway.

01:50.320 --> 01:51.600
Enjoy the breakfast.

02:17.880 --> 02:19.360
Anna.

02:20.160 --> 02:21.400
What's for dessert?

02:23.760 --> 02:24.760
Please bring it.

02:34.360 --> 02:35.160
Thank you!

02:51.000 --> 02:51.880
Please have some.

02:53.040 --> 02:53.840
Gopalan.

02:54.520 --> 02:55.600
A.J.K. and Sameer.

02:56.800 --> 02:57.640
Pooja.

02:58.720 --> 02:59.720
You too, Megha.

03:04.040 --> 03:04.880
Please have some.

03:10.880 --> 03:12.680
Let's celebrate today.

03:17.440 --> 03:18.480
But we've failed, sir.

03:18.720 --> 03:20.320
Yes, we have.

03:21.120 --> 03:22.360
Spectacularly!

03:35.560 --> 03:37.840
So far, the obstacles we faced

03:38.400 --> 03:41.520
while starting Titan

03:41.880 --> 03:43.120
were either related to a loan

03:43.520 --> 03:46.040
or government regulations.

03:46.560 --> 03:48.960
But today, for the first time,

03:50.760 --> 03:52.960
we ourselves
are the reason for our failure.

03:58.000 --> 03:59.680
I think that's worth celebrating.

04:00.720 --> 04:02.760
Celebrating failure means

04:03.040 --> 04:05.520
we're ready
to acknowledge our mistakes.

04:07.560 --> 04:09.320
It becomes easier to move on

04:10.400 --> 04:12.320
and grow faster.

04:14.400 --> 04:16.960
I believe we should
never stop trying.

04:17.680 --> 04:20.960
I believe we deserve
the freedom to fail.

04:22.280 --> 04:23.280
What do you say?

04:23.800 --> 04:25.000
The road to great dreams

04:25.040 --> 04:27.400
passes through great failures.

04:32.760 --> 04:33.560
What do you think?

04:34.920 --> 04:36.400
Do we deserve the freedom to fail?

04:36.640 --> 04:37.480
- Yes, sir.
- Yes!

04:37.520 --> 04:38.960
I'm... I'm sorry.

04:39.040 --> 04:40.600
Do we deserve the freedom to fail?

04:40.640 --> 04:41.840
- Yes, sir!
- Yes!

04:42.280 --> 04:44.680
- To...
- To the freedom to fail!

04:44.760 --> 04:46.400
To the freedom to fail.

04:48.080 --> 04:49.200
To Titan!

04:49.480 --> 04:50.600
To Titan.

04:50.680 --> 04:52.080
- To Titan.
- To Titan.

04:58.240 --> 04:59.600
To failure!

05:19.080 --> 05:19.920
Batteries?

05:21.160 --> 05:22.040
Working.

05:23.720 --> 05:24.800
ECB chip?

05:26.280 --> 05:27.240
It's working.

05:27.880 --> 05:28.680
Quartz?

05:30.200 --> 05:31.400
Quartz is a crystal,

05:31.920 --> 05:33.000
so it can't be faulty.

05:33.680 --> 05:34.560
Coil?

05:36.920 --> 05:37.880
It's working, sir.

05:39.280 --> 05:40.400
Cannon pinion?

05:46.720 --> 05:47.960
It's faulty, sir.

05:50.120 --> 05:51.200
It's covered in metal dust.

05:51.480 --> 05:53.120
"It's covered in metal dust?"

05:57.720 --> 05:58.640
Yours?

06:03.280 --> 06:04.360
The teeth are broken.

06:04.880 --> 06:05.720
They are not working.

06:06.320 --> 06:07.200
Yours?

06:08.880 --> 06:09.960
This is faulty too.

06:16.720 --> 06:17.560
Faulty.

06:21.320 --> 06:23.560
Did the Japanese dealers
supply defective components?

06:25.760 --> 06:26.560
Sir.

06:27.720 --> 06:28.920
We must buy new stock.

06:29.160 --> 06:31.520
Otherwise,
watchmaking is impossible.

06:34.560 --> 06:37.600
Did Ravi check the goods properly?

06:38.120 --> 06:39.520
Check the entire shipment.

06:39.880 --> 06:41.560
Gaurav, come with me.

06:44.280 --> 06:45.840
Gaurav,
I think you should go to Japan.

06:58.040 --> 06:59.240
- Okay, sir.
- Okay. Thank you.

06:59.440 --> 07:00.640
Wait a minute.

07:01.320 --> 07:03.920
Zee, I think
I should go to Japan as well.

07:03.920 --> 07:04.760
Why?

07:04.800 --> 07:06.800
To secure quality consignments,

07:06.840 --> 07:08.840
we'll need to build
business relations with them.

07:09.200 --> 07:12.120
Because, for the Japanese dealers,
we're just another client for now.

07:12.520 --> 07:14.480
What if we need you here?

07:15.000 --> 07:17.280
There's a man who can handle it.

07:17.760 --> 07:18.600
Who?

07:19.000 --> 07:20.280
Xerxes Desai.

07:24.040 --> 07:25.120
Thank you, Gaurav.

07:25.280 --> 07:26.280
What about some tea?

07:26.800 --> 07:28.320
It's about sushi.

07:34.360 --> 07:36.760
- "Five?" How much time
will you need to repair it? - Megha!

07:38.240 --> 07:40.400
- Oh. Are you leaving?
- Yes.

07:41.320 --> 07:44.560
I...
I'll call you after reaching there.

07:46.920 --> 07:48.640
Gaurav, let's go.

07:49.200 --> 07:50.120
Coming, sir!

07:50.600 --> 07:51.400
Huh?

07:51.520 --> 07:52.560
All the best, Gaurav.

07:53.280 --> 07:54.040
Gaurav, hurry up.

07:55.400 --> 07:56.600
We're waiting for...

07:56.600 --> 07:57.560
Thank you, Ravi.

07:57.840 --> 07:58.800
Megha.

07:59.440 --> 08:00.840
- Yes?
- We must find a designer.

08:02.080 --> 08:03.480
Now we have to give Jeh

08:04.240 --> 08:06.880
a fully functional watch,
not a prototype.

08:07.000 --> 08:07.800
Yes, sir.

08:08.080 --> 08:09.320
How soon can you find one?

08:09.840 --> 08:10.920
Two weeks.

08:11.200 --> 08:12.320
You have three days.

08:21.800 --> 08:22.800
Good morning, sir.

08:22.880 --> 08:23.840
Good morning!

08:24.000 --> 08:25.320
Sir, he's our watch designer.

08:26.400 --> 08:27.240
Hello.

08:29.640 --> 08:30.560
But he is...

08:30.680 --> 08:33.360
Yes, sir. Just like
the film 'Seeta Aur Geeta'.

08:33.360 --> 08:34.360
'Ram Aur Shyam'...

08:35.600 --> 08:38.000
He's Mr. Devendra Naik's
twin brother, Mr. Ravindra Naik.

08:39.240 --> 08:41.240
I already owe your brother.
Now I will owe you.

08:41.320 --> 08:42.280
Don't bother, sir.

08:43.200 --> 08:45.920
- Sir, he's from
the J.J. School of Arts. - Oh!

08:46.640 --> 08:49.360
When did you graduate?

08:49.400 --> 08:50.360
1970, sir.

08:50.440 --> 08:53.360
So, did you meet
Gaitonde and Padamse?

08:53.400 --> 08:54.800
Of course!
They were my seniors, sir.

08:55.480 --> 08:56.480
Fantastic.

08:56.920 --> 08:58.440
Fantastic! It's so good to have you.

08:58.720 --> 08:59.760
Pleasure is mine, sir.

09:07.200 --> 09:09.960
So, is there any progress?

09:10.960 --> 09:12.040
I'm on it, sir.

09:12.600 --> 09:15.040
Sir, these are GMT's designs.
We...

09:15.240 --> 09:18.120
We still don't know exactly
what we want to make,

09:18.520 --> 09:20.080
but we should at least know

09:20.840 --> 09:22.440
what we don't want to make,
shouldn't we?

09:42.160 --> 09:43.240
Have you seen 'Pyaasa'?

09:43.520 --> 09:44.880
- 'Pyaasa', the film?
- Hmm.

09:45.000 --> 09:46.400
- I have seen it 13 times.
- Oh.

09:46.680 --> 09:50.080
'Pyaasa' is a serious
and tragic film.

09:50.080 --> 09:50.880
Yes.

09:50.920 --> 09:53.360
But the film features an upbeat,

09:53.400 --> 09:54.760
cheerful song.

09:54.840 --> 09:55.680
Right.

09:55.760 --> 09:57.960
- "When your head feels heavy..."
- "When your head feels heavy..."

09:58.080 --> 10:00.640
- "Or when you're sorrowful."
- "Or when you're sorrowful."

10:00.800 --> 10:03.480
- "Then please come to me."
- "Then please come to me."

10:03.520 --> 10:06.200
- "Don't be scared."
- "Don't be scared."

10:06.240 --> 10:07.640
- "Don't be scared."
- "Don't be scared."

10:07.720 --> 10:08.920
Mr. Rafi sang wonderfully!

10:10.080 --> 10:12.440
The tragedy in 'Pyaasa'

10:12.520 --> 10:15.520
becomes even more striking against
the contrast of this happiness.

10:16.480 --> 10:17.720
- Contrast is very powerful.
- Yes.

10:17.960 --> 10:18.920
- Right?
- Of course, sir.

10:19.040 --> 10:22.120
It balances and highlights nuances.

10:22.840 --> 10:23.720
- Right.
- Right?

10:24.040 --> 10:25.560
In my opinion,

10:25.880 --> 10:28.360
the bezel should be grander,

10:29.600 --> 10:32.360
while the watch face,
dial, and strap

10:32.520 --> 10:34.080
should be simpler.

10:34.360 --> 10:35.360
Elegant!

10:35.760 --> 10:37.400
Let the contrast speak.

10:39.280 --> 10:40.760
- I think you're right.
- Hmm.

10:41.200 --> 10:43.200
- Okay, I'll work on it.
- Hmm.

10:47.360 --> 10:48.280
Hello!

10:52.120 --> 10:52.920
What?

10:57.440 --> 10:58.280
What the...

11:06.040 --> 11:07.760
- Hello, Gaurav.
'- Yes, sir.'

11:08.040 --> 11:10.800
The Japanese translator
has fallen ill.

11:11.080 --> 11:11.880
'Oh.'

11:13.760 --> 11:15.360
'No worries, sir.
I'll find a solution.'

11:35.880 --> 11:38.000
Has he gone all the way
to India to find a translator?

11:38.600 --> 11:40.160
[in Japanese] Do you know Japanese?

11:40.960 --> 11:42.160
Huh.

11:48.240 --> 11:50.200
[in Japanese]
I'm sorry for the delay, sir.

11:50.840 --> 11:52.280
My name is Gaurav.

11:52.400 --> 11:55.120
We both are from Tata.

11:55.400 --> 11:57.120
Greetings! Please be seated.

11:59.000 --> 12:00.600
- [in Japanese] Thank you.
- Thank you.

12:00.720 --> 12:02.320
Do you know Japanese as well?

12:02.840 --> 12:04.240
Thanks to a student exchange
programme, sir.

12:04.680 --> 12:05.480
Wonderful!

12:06.960 --> 12:08.880
[in Japanese]
I'm sorry for the magnets.

12:09.920 --> 12:12.880
- How can we make it right?
- It's okay, Mr. Yuto.

12:14.240 --> 12:16.440
[in Japanese] But this time,

12:16.720 --> 12:19.800
we need to inspect the consignment
before the delivery.

12:20.560 --> 12:22.880
[in Japanese]
I understand your concern,

12:23.360 --> 12:25.680
but that is not covered
by our terms and conditions.

12:26.600 --> 12:28.360
[in Japanese]
Gaurav, we won't let you inspect.

12:33.040 --> 12:34.520
Sir, he is saying that,

12:34.960 --> 12:36.360
we can't inspect the components.

12:36.400 --> 12:38.400
according to their
terms and conditions,

12:46.920 --> 12:50.200
Tell him that we can't have
a deal without an inspection.

12:50.880 --> 12:51.840
Sir...

12:56.800 --> 12:59.200
[in Japanese]
We can't have this deal

12:59.920 --> 13:02.320
without an inspection.

13:03.840 --> 13:06.560
[in Japanese] Fine. It's your wish.

13:07.520 --> 13:08.360
Huh?

13:09.360 --> 13:12.000
Sir, he's saying,
"Fine. Let's cancel the deal".

13:24.760 --> 13:25.920
India believes that,

13:26.760 --> 13:29.240
regardless of how a deal unfolds,

13:30.000 --> 13:32.440
relationships should
always be cherished.

13:35.440 --> 13:37.080
We believe every good relationship
should begin

13:37.080 --> 13:38.040
with a sweet.

13:38.080 --> 13:40.200
But I suppose here,

13:41.120 --> 13:42.800
we are going to end one with it.

13:48.240 --> 13:49.600
[in Japanese]
With due respect, what is this?

13:50.840 --> 13:53.360
[in Japanese]
These are sweets, Mr. Yuto.

13:54.880 --> 13:57.520
Just as you have tarts,

13:58.720 --> 14:00.360
we have 'laddus'.

14:01.920 --> 14:04.000
[in Japanese] Please try one.

14:04.480 --> 14:05.640
[in Japanese] Thank you.

14:14.720 --> 14:15.880
- Thank you.
- Wait!

14:16.680 --> 14:19.400
Our terms and conditions
don't allow an inspection,

14:20.720 --> 14:22.520
but we can make an exception.

14:28.320 --> 14:29.400
If he knew English so well,

14:29.440 --> 14:30.680
why hasn't he
been speaking it all this time?

14:31.000 --> 14:32.360
Sir, my knowledge was tested too.

14:32.480 --> 14:34.240
Please sit. Be seated.

14:37.080 --> 14:38.000
Mr. Yuto,

14:39.320 --> 14:41.360
this is going to be
your best decision.

14:42.080 --> 14:43.840
[speaking in Japanese]

14:46.000 --> 14:48.440
- Good evening, Ravindra.
- Good evening!

14:48.880 --> 14:50.920
I tried to find
some inspiration for you.

14:51.120 --> 14:52.960
Each element is slightly different.

14:53.200 --> 14:55.080
- Yes. - Yet look at
the contrasting styles.

14:55.200 --> 14:58.280
- This is a completely different,
busier style. - Oh, yes.

14:58.320 --> 15:00.320
Right?
What if each hand looked like this?

15:00.640 --> 15:02.000
- Sharp.
- "Sharp!"

15:02.800 --> 15:04.720
Whereas this was done
by the same designer.

15:04.760 --> 15:05.800
The same designer!

15:05.800 --> 15:07.400
- Yes. - And yet,
look at the contrasting style.

15:07.400 --> 15:11.040
- Hmm! - Brutalism
is a good source of inspiration.

15:34.600 --> 15:35.920
It is

15:37.360 --> 15:38.400
perfect!

15:39.680 --> 15:40.760
- Thank you!
- I love it.

15:49.320 --> 15:50.600
I love the way you sketch.

15:51.080 --> 15:52.360
It's classic.

15:52.560 --> 15:54.880
It's timeless.

15:55.560 --> 15:57.040
That's what we should call it.

15:58.680 --> 15:59.880
Classique.

16:00.440 --> 16:01.680
Classique?

16:04.360 --> 16:05.600
When will you give me
some more designs?

16:07.480 --> 16:08.520
More designs?

16:19.880 --> 16:20.640
Bye!

16:30.800 --> 16:32.640
Megha, it's okay to be angry,

16:34.000 --> 16:36.120
but do you really think

16:36.520 --> 16:38.920
your mother is entirely wrong?

16:40.560 --> 16:42.600
I don't know that. All I know
is that I don't want to get married.

16:44.160 --> 16:45.960
Sometimes, we desire something,

16:46.760 --> 16:49.120
even though what we
truly need is something else.

16:51.440 --> 16:53.480
So, Megha, think twice

16:54.520 --> 16:55.760
before making a decision,

16:57.920 --> 16:59.800
because it's not easy to live alone.

17:13.160 --> 17:15.640
You've incorporated
all the feedback perfectly.

17:16.320 --> 17:18.960
The bracelet looks sleek.
It's perfect.

17:19.000 --> 17:21.360
- And look at the bezel.
- Yes, sir.

17:21.400 --> 17:22.240
Very good.

17:22.640 --> 17:24.480
- Approved!
- Oh! Thank you.

17:24.960 --> 17:26.080
It's a bold design.

17:26.120 --> 17:28.720
- I think it'll attract
our young customers. - Hmm.

17:29.160 --> 17:30.440
What should we call it?

17:32.560 --> 17:35.920
- Young...
- Something for people on the move.

17:35.920 --> 17:36.920
On the go.

17:37.160 --> 17:38.920
Fast! Fast-paced?

17:41.640 --> 17:43.040
No, something sporty.

17:45.560 --> 17:46.440
Hello!

17:46.800 --> 17:48.400
'- Megha?'
- Gaurav?

17:49.160 --> 17:50.760
How are you?
Where are you calling from?

17:50.800 --> 17:51.920
Japan... I'm calling from Japan.

17:51.960 --> 17:53.120
I'm at the hotel.

17:54.280 --> 17:55.480
How was the deal?

17:55.640 --> 17:56.640
It was about to be ruined

17:56.680 --> 17:58.920
when Akash played his trump card.

17:59.440 --> 18:00.720
'He gave him the 'laddus'
made by your mother.'

18:01.360 --> 18:03.280
'Those 'laddus' did the trick,
Megha.'

18:03.520 --> 18:05.240
- Believe me...
- Gaurav.

18:05.840 --> 18:07.480
It's getting late,
and we have a flight to catch.

18:08.920 --> 18:10.720
Yes. Um...

18:11.000 --> 18:12.200
I need to go.

18:12.920 --> 18:14.840
'- Gaurav, please come!
- I'm ready, sir!'

18:14.920 --> 18:17.080
- Yes... See you tomorrow.
'- See you tomorrow.'

18:17.120 --> 18:18.240
- Bye.
'- Bye!'

18:28.920 --> 18:29.720
Hello?

18:29.840 --> 18:31.280
Should I get something for you?

18:34.960 --> 18:36.480
Anything will do, Gaurav.

18:36.560 --> 18:38.760
Don't be like this. Please tell me.

18:39.320 --> 18:41.000
- You decide.
- We're running late.

18:41.040 --> 18:42.000
- Genuinely...
- Sir, just a minute.

18:42.080 --> 18:43.920
Sir, what are you doing?
I'm coming, sir.

18:44.000 --> 18:45.720
- You've been fooling me.
- I'll call you later.

18:46.160 --> 18:47.640
'Sir, give me a minute.
I'm coming, sir.'

18:47.840 --> 18:49.000
Bye.

18:54.880 --> 18:56.440
Shall I bring you
a bottle of perfume?

18:56.520 --> 18:58.280
'I saw them at the airport.'

18:58.360 --> 18:59.040
Gaurav.

18:59.080 --> 19:00.960
- 'You may take the bus.
I'm leaving.' - Sir, I'm done!

19:01.080 --> 19:03.040
- Sorry! Perfume... Bye!
- Bye!

19:07.560 --> 19:09.200
Gaurav, I don't need anything.
You just...

19:10.960 --> 19:13.520
Oh. Uh, yes. Yes, sir is here.

19:13.680 --> 19:14.680
Just a minute.

19:15.760 --> 19:17.520
Sir, there's a call
from Bombay House.

19:18.240 --> 19:20.120
- One second.
- Yes. Okay.

19:28.400 --> 19:29.240
Hello?

19:30.560 --> 19:31.520
Yes?

19:49.320 --> 19:50.480
Sir!

19:51.600 --> 19:52.760
Sir!

19:54.640 --> 19:56.160
What's the matter, sir?

19:59.400 --> 20:00.560
Jeh...

20:01.440 --> 20:02.960
- All okay?
- Jeh...

20:04.400 --> 20:05.840
Jeh had a heart attack.

20:37.040 --> 20:38.080
How's he?

20:39.400 --> 20:40.400
Stable,

20:41.320 --> 20:42.560
but not very well.

20:44.960 --> 20:46.320
Did anyone inform Ms. Thelma?

20:46.600 --> 20:47.840
She's on her way.

20:48.760 --> 20:50.040
She's on the way here.

20:51.160 --> 20:52.520
The doctors said

20:53.200 --> 20:55.040
it will take him
some time to wake up.

21:01.000 --> 21:03.600
I can't go
into the office without you.

21:03.680 --> 21:04.680
I can't!

21:07.320 --> 21:08.480
I can't.

21:21.840 --> 21:22.800
Yes, Mr. Desai.

21:23.840 --> 21:25.480
It'll be done. Don't worry.

21:29.360 --> 21:32.800
So, J.R.D. is stable now.

21:34.200 --> 21:35.040
Thank God!

21:35.880 --> 21:40.080
But Mr. Desai is worried
about the work scenario here.

21:40.640 --> 21:41.640
We are here for that.

21:42.480 --> 21:44.320
The components have arrived.
We're good to go.

21:44.400 --> 21:47.000
Designs, sir.
Xerxes needs some more designs.

21:47.280 --> 21:49.320
So, what are we waiting for?

21:50.000 --> 21:51.600
We need to broaden our vision

21:52.400 --> 21:54.520
to create world-class designs.

21:55.520 --> 21:58.360
A major watch expo will be held
in Europe in ten days.

21:58.440 --> 22:00.120
All the international brands
will be there,

22:00.480 --> 22:02.400
exhibiting their latest products.

22:02.600 --> 22:03.880
I believe

22:04.440 --> 22:06.760
one of us should go there
for a few days.

22:07.080 --> 22:09.160
It's imperative to know

22:09.400 --> 22:10.680
what's happening internationally.

22:12.320 --> 22:13.640
I think you should go.

22:14.000 --> 22:15.600
I'm not really sure about that.

22:17.160 --> 22:20.080
Mr. Gopalan, our watch will set
the standard for our country.

22:20.800 --> 22:22.920
If we want to compete
with international standards,

22:22.960 --> 22:24.840
attending the expo is essential.

22:25.400 --> 22:28.080
Honestly, I think right now
we should focus on growth

22:29.080 --> 22:30.760
rather than funding.

22:31.080 --> 22:34.200
So you're saying I don't care
about the company's growth?

22:41.080 --> 22:43.080
Mr. Gopalan,
you know I didn't mean it that way.

22:47.680 --> 22:48.520
All right.

22:50.160 --> 22:51.440
Go ahead and send him.

22:52.520 --> 22:53.520
Happy?

23:02.360 --> 23:04.480
- Have a safe trip. Hmm?
- Yes.

23:04.600 --> 23:05.440
I will.

23:20.080 --> 23:21.920
- How are you feeling?
- Wonderful.

23:22.000 --> 23:23.240
Thank you very much.

23:24.680 --> 23:25.800
Please don't worry.

23:26.160 --> 23:27.360
He'll be fine.

23:30.840 --> 23:32.240
- Sir.
- Hello, Pinks!

23:32.440 --> 23:33.520
- Good morning, sir.
- Morning.

23:33.640 --> 23:34.600
Your signature, please.

23:39.320 --> 23:40.840
It was amazing!

23:40.920 --> 23:43.040
- Huh? - The entire auditorium
was jam-packed.

23:43.120 --> 23:44.640
- I see.
- Please give it to me.

23:46.040 --> 23:47.040
Please take this one.

23:47.240 --> 23:49.040
Imagine a fourteen-year-old writing

23:49.080 --> 23:51.400
so beautifully
on political diversity.

23:51.600 --> 23:53.280
Wait! Was the play written by her?

23:53.360 --> 23:55.280
Your daughter is an amazing writer.

23:55.800 --> 23:56.840
- Don't you have spinach?
- Wow!

23:56.880 --> 23:58.000
You'll get it tomorrow.

23:58.840 --> 24:00.840
And in the end,
she got a standing ovation.

24:00.960 --> 24:02.520
- Oh!
- You should have been there.

24:14.640 --> 24:15.720
- Ravi.
- Yes, sir.

24:15.880 --> 24:17.520
I need all the expense sheets

24:17.560 --> 24:18.680
from the accounts department
by this evening.

24:29.000 --> 24:29.920
Relax.
- Time...

24:29.960 --> 24:31.840
- Do you need water?
- We don't have time, Akash.

24:31.920 --> 24:32.720
We are late.

24:32.840 --> 24:34.640
Okay? Only two designs are ready.

24:39.080 --> 24:41.040
This will never stop.

24:42.480 --> 24:43.400
It's fully tested.

24:47.360 --> 24:48.160
Hmm!

24:53.640 --> 24:55.280
Sir, these are the new designs.

25:04.560 --> 25:06.920
Actually, Akash suggested

25:07.120 --> 25:09.280
that the designers be sent
to the watch expo in Europe

25:09.600 --> 25:11.680
so they could create
world-class designs.

25:12.760 --> 25:13.640
Hmm.

25:16.520 --> 25:18.440
How are the designs, Mr. Desai?

25:22.880 --> 25:24.680
I suppose I'm going back to Bombay.

25:28.520 --> 25:31.120
- Jeh should see this.
- Yes, sir.

25:34.000 --> 25:34.920
Great job!

25:35.520 --> 25:36.520
Thank you.

25:46.880 --> 25:47.800
Hi, Jeh!

25:48.280 --> 25:49.440
Hello, Zee.

25:50.320 --> 25:52.840
- You're looking fitter than before.
- Yes.

25:52.960 --> 25:56.280
A walk a day keeps the doctor away.

25:57.800 --> 25:59.200
I have brought you something.

26:06.440 --> 26:08.760
- Looks nice, but...
- No.

26:09.560 --> 26:11.840
- It'll never stop.
- Uh-huh.

26:14.880 --> 26:17.760
Whether or not your watch stops,

26:17.880 --> 26:19.480
I’m not going anywhere.

26:21.960 --> 26:23.280
Here are our designs.

26:26.120 --> 26:28.760
Excellent, Zee. Excellent!

26:29.480 --> 26:30.880
Aha!

26:30.880 --> 26:32.960
Very good. Very nice.

26:33.120 --> 26:34.920
I should have
a heart attack more often.

26:35.880 --> 26:36.840
Jeh...

26:40.000 --> 26:42.000
When should I present this
to the Titan Board?

26:42.080 --> 26:44.720
This isn't meant for a boardroom,

26:46.480 --> 26:48.240
but for a ballroom.

26:49.640 --> 26:50.480
Very well.

26:51.120 --> 26:53.160
I'll talk to Pinks.

27:02.160 --> 27:03.360
How's Uncle?

27:04.640 --> 27:05.480
He's fine.

27:05.960 --> 27:07.600
How's his Alzheimer's treatment?

27:09.280 --> 27:11.120
He has started calling
Kumud by Mom's name.

27:12.320 --> 27:14.320
I'm so lucky to have
Kumud in my life, Zee.

27:14.360 --> 27:15.360
I can't even begin to tell you.

27:16.560 --> 27:18.680
Still, I give time
to neither Dad nor her.

27:18.800 --> 27:21.360
Look, take some time off.

27:21.560 --> 27:22.400
Okay?

27:22.440 --> 27:24.880
Uncle and Vihaan need you.

27:28.040 --> 27:29.480
You need a vacation too.

27:29.800 --> 27:31.680
Listen, I'm with you.

27:32.200 --> 27:33.080
I'll be here.

27:33.200 --> 27:35.120
So, you should take a few days off.

27:35.160 --> 27:36.760
You should take a few days off.

27:36.840 --> 27:37.960
It's you who should
take a few days off!

27:38.000 --> 27:40.440
- You take a few days off.
- Stop it.

27:41.520 --> 27:42.360
- Sir.
- Hmm?

27:42.760 --> 27:43.920
Actually...

27:44.800 --> 27:48.600
Sameer, Pooja and A.J.K. are doing
great in the manufacturing sector.

27:48.800 --> 27:49.600
Yes.

27:49.640 --> 27:52.040
May I handle

27:52.920 --> 27:55.600
another part of the business?

27:56.320 --> 27:58.840
Like sales and marketing.

27:59.840 --> 28:00.880
May I?

28:07.040 --> 28:07.960
Sure.

28:09.120 --> 28:10.320
Thank you, sir.

28:12.080 --> 28:16.800
Sir, I've agreed to meet the suitors
suggested by my mother.

28:17.720 --> 28:19.360
- Is it?
- Really?

28:24.960 --> 28:27.880
I mean... Very good.
Congratulations.

28:28.480 --> 28:29.320
I'm happy for you.

28:33.880 --> 28:36.040
May I have your attention, please?

28:36.560 --> 28:38.600
Ladies and gentlemen, just a moment.

28:41.000 --> 28:42.560
I have no words

28:43.320 --> 28:45.960
to express my joy

28:46.520 --> 28:48.840
at seeing everyone
who has been involved

28:48.880 --> 28:52.200
with Titan since the very
first meeting here today.

28:54.800 --> 28:58.200
So, I'm truly proud to present

28:59.440 --> 29:00.360
this,

29:01.480 --> 29:03.880
made by Indians,

29:05.520 --> 29:06.840
for Indians!

29:18.280 --> 29:20.200
Presenting Exacta.

29:24.560 --> 29:26.000
Royale.

29:28.320 --> 29:29.600
Classique.

29:33.760 --> 29:35.040
And Fastrack.

29:52.400 --> 29:54.640
Desai, these look amazing.

29:55.120 --> 29:55.960
Thank you, sir. Thank you.

29:56.000 --> 29:59.920
But the credit goes to my engineers
and my wonderful team.

30:00.960 --> 30:03.080
The designs are beautiful,

30:03.080 --> 30:04.880
but I'm not sure

30:05.520 --> 30:07.480
they can compete with GMT.

30:08.440 --> 30:09.920
They will, sir.

30:10.640 --> 30:12.400
I appreciate your confidence.

30:18.680 --> 30:21.280
Can you tell me the exact numbers?

30:23.320 --> 30:24.680
Which exact numbers?

30:25.640 --> 30:27.480
How many watches

30:27.960 --> 30:29.960
will you be able to sell during
the first month of the launch?

30:35.280 --> 30:36.600
Two thousand.

30:39.480 --> 30:40.760
Twenty thousand, sir.

30:46.760 --> 30:47.600
Are you sure?

30:47.760 --> 30:48.920
Quite sure.

30:53.680 --> 30:55.880
- All the best.
- Thank you very much.

31:07.160 --> 31:10.320
The MD seems really confident.

31:11.000 --> 31:12.600
It seems the distribution network

31:12.720 --> 31:14.360
has now reached
across the entire country.

31:14.840 --> 31:17.040
Not yet, sir, but it will.

31:17.200 --> 31:18.320
Don't worry.

31:19.600 --> 31:21.600
India is ready for Titan.

31:22.560 --> 31:24.600
- You'll never change.
- Quiet.

31:28.960 --> 31:30.240
Very good.

31:36.800 --> 31:37.760
I'm almost there.

31:39.200 --> 31:40.080
Let's go, sir.

31:54.120 --> 31:55.160
Shall we?

32:34.160 --> 32:35.520
Sir, it runs on quartz technology

32:35.600 --> 32:36.960
and carries the trust of Tata.

32:37.440 --> 32:38.840
It will change your life.

32:39.200 --> 32:40.560
I don't understand this technology.

32:40.600 --> 32:42.080
Please look at the design first.

32:42.320 --> 32:43.760
It has been entirely made in India.

32:44.080 --> 32:46.600
Sir, please try to understand.

32:47.040 --> 32:48.760
Everything changes with time.

32:49.280 --> 32:52.440
Quartz is the future of Bharat.

32:52.720 --> 32:54.240
Why create problems

32:55.080 --> 32:55.960
when everything is going smoothly?

32:56.000 --> 32:57.000
I know,

32:57.200 --> 32:59.040
but what's the harm
in trying just once?

32:59.040 --> 33:00.880
We are quite happy and content
distributing GMT watches.

33:04.600 --> 33:05.600
I'm sorry.

33:23.000 --> 33:25.320
'Zee, the watches
aren't selling at all.'

33:28.480 --> 33:29.280
Okay.

33:30.000 --> 33:32.920
I think the distributors don't
appreciate our product enough.

33:35.400 --> 33:37.360
Why should I replace
the watches in my store?

33:37.520 --> 33:39.600
Sir, try replacing them once.

33:39.600 --> 33:41.000
I bet it will change your life.

33:41.120 --> 33:43.040
Please keep four pieces for now.

33:43.320 --> 33:44.920
I guarantee that you'll
end up ordering 400 more.

33:45.000 --> 33:46.320
Ma'am, you should be
looking after the house.

33:46.880 --> 33:48.600
Leave the business side to us.

33:48.680 --> 33:50.840
- Oi! Be respectful!
- Gaurav.

33:51.640 --> 33:52.880
I agree, sir.

33:52.960 --> 33:54.680
No one's ready to take the risk.

33:58.440 --> 34:01.360
Sir, it will take some time
for sales to pick up.

34:01.680 --> 34:03.240
Please keep these
for a few more days.

34:03.400 --> 34:05.120
No one is buying your watches.

34:05.160 --> 34:06.880
Listen to me, leave this job

34:07.080 --> 34:08.200
and join GMT.

34:08.600 --> 34:09.760
Everyone prefers GMT.

34:11.080 --> 34:11.880
Take it back.

34:13.720 --> 34:14.680
Sir...

34:18.200 --> 34:19.200
Gaurav!

34:20.360 --> 34:21.600
Did you recognise me?

34:22.160 --> 34:23.600
Avinash!

34:25.640 --> 34:28.960
An IIT graduate and
an academic topper, Gaurav Dhar!

34:30.240 --> 34:32.520
What are you doing with a carton?

34:33.240 --> 34:34.600
You won't understand.

34:34.880 --> 34:35.960
Please make me understand.

34:36.120 --> 34:37.200
I found out

34:37.400 --> 34:39.360
that you work for the Tatas.

34:39.680 --> 34:42.240
So what's all this about?

34:45.520 --> 34:46.840
What's going on, my friend?

34:47.560 --> 34:50.200
Do you remember how my grandfather

34:51.080 --> 34:53.080
used to hand us machines

34:53.640 --> 34:54.840
to repair?

34:55.080 --> 34:56.240
Of course I remember.

34:56.840 --> 34:58.560
That's why we avoided visiting you.

34:59.520 --> 35:01.760
We were afraid he might
entrust us with some work.

35:02.960 --> 35:04.600
One day, he gave me a watch.

35:06.000 --> 35:07.160
It was my mother's.

35:09.720 --> 35:11.200
She always wore it

35:11.440 --> 35:12.560
and never took it off.

35:14.640 --> 35:16.280
Even on the day she passed away.

35:17.360 --> 35:19.080
I remember her wearing it.

35:22.600 --> 35:24.040
When I saw that watch,

35:25.320 --> 35:26.760
I started crying.

35:28.280 --> 35:29.840
My hands started shaking.

35:30.080 --> 35:31.320
I said,

35:31.960 --> 35:33.400
"I cannot fix this."

35:35.240 --> 35:36.800
It was such a tiny machine.

35:41.400 --> 35:43.680
My grandfather
took out his magnifying glass

35:44.800 --> 35:46.400
and fixed it in ten minutes.

35:50.960 --> 35:52.520
The moment it started working,

35:56.160 --> 35:57.360
I felt

36:00.040 --> 36:00.920
like...

36:09.960 --> 36:11.280
I don't know what it was,
but something changed.

36:14.200 --> 36:15.160
That was the day I realised

36:15.200 --> 36:16.880
engineers could fix
anything in the world.

36:31.080 --> 36:32.760
Our company's name is Titan.

36:48.200 --> 36:50.960
We'll distribute Titan watches.

36:53.480 --> 36:57.600
Let's open
the very first Titan store.

36:58.440 --> 37:00.800
- Right from production
to distribution? - Yes.

37:01.040 --> 37:02.160
A store

37:02.840 --> 37:05.160
where watches
are sold like diamonds.

37:05.560 --> 37:09.120
Our product will get
the respect it deserves.

37:09.880 --> 37:11.120
And I respect this watch.

37:11.160 --> 37:13.000
It's a world-class watch!

37:13.120 --> 37:14.560
- Right?
- Absolutely, sir.

37:14.640 --> 37:15.680
Without a doubt.

37:17.080 --> 37:21.080
Come on, let's prove
its worth to the world.

37:23.040 --> 37:23.880
Correct, sir.

37:24.440 --> 37:25.840
The World of Titan.

37:32.680 --> 37:33.960
Whoa!

37:51.120 --> 37:54.280
Man! It seems we'll sell out
the entire stock in a single day.

37:55.160 --> 37:58.000
May God bless your words.

38:11.520 --> 38:12.880
Sir, you don't need to wind it.

38:12.920 --> 38:14.800
This watch runs on a battery.

38:14.960 --> 38:15.760
What do you mean?

38:15.800 --> 38:18.120
This is a quartz watch,
not a mechanical watch.

38:18.480 --> 38:19.840
You don't have to do anything.

38:19.920 --> 38:21.120
Just wear it.

38:21.280 --> 38:23.840
You only have to change
the battery every two years.

38:23.920 --> 38:27.160
Ma'am, even the number
of breaths we have

38:27.200 --> 38:28.600
is limited.

38:28.840 --> 38:31.240
I don't want to trouble myself
with a battery.

38:31.280 --> 38:33.840
Sir, these days
even toys run on batteries.

38:34.040 --> 38:36.640
This watch is much better
than a mechanical one.

38:36.680 --> 38:37.920
Please try one.

38:38.040 --> 38:40.960
No. If you don't have
a mechanical watch,

38:41.000 --> 38:43.280
I won't buy one. I'm leaving.

38:43.320 --> 38:44.640
You can keep this.

38:49.920 --> 38:50.880
Mom!

38:52.960 --> 38:54.240
How come you're here?

38:54.360 --> 38:55.480
I missed you.

38:57.960 --> 38:58.960
I'm fine.

39:00.320 --> 39:02.200
- He's Gaurav.
- Namaste!

39:02.240 --> 39:03.920
Namaste! Please come with me.

39:04.120 --> 39:06.040
- Where?
- Let's meet the boy.

39:06.280 --> 39:08.320
He lives in Hosur.

39:11.280 --> 39:12.240
You'll like him.

39:12.280 --> 39:13.840
Mom, it's a big day for me,
yet you...

39:14.000 --> 39:16.680
So what?
Your team will handle everything.

39:19.480 --> 39:20.480
Come on, let's go!

39:20.640 --> 39:22.640
He has taken the day off today.

39:23.800 --> 39:26.880
He's waiting for you
at your factory.

39:27.520 --> 39:29.680
I'll leave tonight. Hmm?

39:31.560 --> 39:32.400
Let's go.

39:34.520 --> 39:35.560
Come on!

39:43.800 --> 39:45.400
Hi, Megha! Hi, Aunt!

39:45.400 --> 39:46.280
Please sit.

39:48.160 --> 39:50.440
So, Megha,
tell me something about yourself.

39:51.440 --> 39:53.360
You have a stressful life
and a demanding job.

39:53.600 --> 39:55.800
Aunt, am I right?

39:56.720 --> 39:58.680
But the money's good.

39:59.680 --> 40:00.920
Ladies should work too,

40:01.000 --> 40:02.240
but they need to find a balance.

40:02.320 --> 40:04.680
Actually, the household chores
need attention as well.

40:04.960 --> 40:06.400
Right, Aunt?

40:06.400 --> 40:08.120
[in Kannada] I like that.
Don't leave your job.

40:08.400 --> 40:09.760
You should continue working.

40:10.000 --> 40:11.320
Times have changed.

40:11.440 --> 40:12.720
We need to study hard.

40:12.760 --> 40:14.360
I work for a big company.

40:14.400 --> 40:15.960
Do you work for the Tatas?
The watch-making company Titan.

40:15.960 --> 40:16.760
Good! Good!

40:31.400 --> 40:32.720
We sold seven watches.

40:34.240 --> 40:36.520
Around 200 to 300 people
came into the store,

40:36.560 --> 40:37.560
yet only seven watches were sold.

40:37.760 --> 40:39.240
Actually, there were
even more people.

40:41.720 --> 40:45.280
There's a huge gap
between walk-ins and the sales rate.

40:48.560 --> 40:50.280
It's okay. Don't worry.

40:51.080 --> 40:52.520
We just have to be patient.

40:53.240 --> 40:54.560
Zee, I have a flight.

40:54.800 --> 40:56.400
- Oh! - I have a flight, everybody.
I'll see you.

40:56.480 --> 40:57.280
- Yes!
- Bye!

40:57.320 --> 40:58.120
Bye!

40:58.200 --> 40:59.560
- Bye, ma'am.
- See you.

40:59.600 --> 41:00.480
Let me walk you out.

41:02.960 --> 41:04.480
Actually, please stay here.
The car's waiting outside.

41:04.520 --> 41:06.200
- No! No! No! I'll drop you off.
- No, it's okay.

41:06.520 --> 41:07.640
These guys need you.

41:08.440 --> 41:09.840
And it'll all be fine.

41:10.120 --> 41:11.120
I hope so.

41:12.360 --> 41:13.480
All the best.

41:16.040 --> 41:17.320
- Bye! Have a safe journey.
- Yes.

41:42.400 --> 41:43.640
What's the time?

41:44.240 --> 41:45.640
It's 12 noon, sir.

41:47.960 --> 41:49.920
Akash should have been here by now.

41:50.320 --> 41:53.160
Without him, we can't present
the complete sales report.

41:55.080 --> 41:57.080
We can't keep the board
waiting any longer.

41:57.320 --> 41:58.520
We'll go.

42:05.880 --> 42:06.680
Desai.

42:06.760 --> 42:10.000
Sir, we can't judge this on
the basis of just two months' sales.

42:10.200 --> 42:12.800
We will make progress.
I guarantee it.

42:13.040 --> 42:15.200
Only 303 watches
were sold in the first month,

42:15.760 --> 42:18.240
and 535 in the second month.

42:18.600 --> 42:21.040
This is barely 5%
of what you promised.

42:21.480 --> 42:23.040
Yes, I know.

42:23.360 --> 42:26.040
We didn't give the green light
to your Watch Project

42:26.160 --> 42:28.280
based solely on your speech.

42:28.960 --> 42:30.760
You promised us more.

42:31.200 --> 42:32.200
Where is it?

42:33.160 --> 42:37.640
I believe people
didn't understand quartz.

42:39.320 --> 42:41.840
Should we consider
the investment in Titan

42:42.600 --> 42:43.520
a loss?

42:43.640 --> 42:45.360
No, sir. Just because

42:45.760 --> 42:48.480
we've started slowly
doesn't mean we won't finish strong.

42:48.480 --> 42:50.440
If this project fails,

42:51.160 --> 42:53.120
who will be responsible
for the loans?

42:53.360 --> 42:54.360
Exactly!

42:54.520 --> 42:58.960
I suggest we first halt
watch manufacturing in Hosur.

42:59.280 --> 43:01.000
First, let's figure out

43:01.120 --> 43:02.400
how to sell the watches

43:02.560 --> 43:03.680
we've already manufactured.

43:03.800 --> 43:05.960
Sorry, gentlemen, I'm late.

43:06.720 --> 43:08.040
This is the sales report
for the third month.

43:14.720 --> 43:18.120
In the third month, we sold
200 watches in Maharashtra,

43:18.600 --> 43:20.040
and 127 in Delhi.

43:21.000 --> 43:25.000
However, 3,029 watches
were sold in Tamil Nadu,

43:25.320 --> 43:28.640
and 4,023 in Karnataka.

43:29.080 --> 43:30.840
- What?
- Yes!

43:33.720 --> 43:35.280
How's this possible?

43:36.000 --> 43:38.600
I'm also wondering
why there's such a huge difference

43:38.640 --> 43:40.000
between sales
in the North and the South.

43:41.480 --> 43:43.520
Desai, are your designs

43:43.560 --> 43:46.120
more relevant in South India?

43:47.920 --> 43:49.600
No, I don't think so.

43:50.080 --> 43:50.960
Do you?

43:52.040 --> 43:53.240
Not at all, sir.

43:54.800 --> 43:56.360
Then why is this happening?

43:57.880 --> 44:01.360
Do our designs actually have
a touch of South India?

44:01.920 --> 44:04.000
No, that's ridiculous.

44:04.360 --> 44:06.040
Our designs are international.

44:06.360 --> 44:07.560
It's something else.

44:08.200 --> 44:10.520
Sir, the northern region sold

44:11.280 --> 44:14.240
7, 10, and 11 watches yesterday.

44:14.640 --> 44:15.920
A total of 28 watches were sold.

44:15.920 --> 44:17.520
I can't make sense of this.

44:18.160 --> 44:20.520
Ms. Megha, your mother's here.

44:21.960 --> 44:23.240
Mom...

44:26.520 --> 44:27.360
Mom.

44:28.320 --> 44:29.280
What's the matter?

44:30.440 --> 44:31.560
Is this how you greet your mother

44:31.600 --> 44:32.680
after not seeing her
for three months?

44:33.760 --> 44:34.720
Uh!

44:35.840 --> 44:37.240
I mean, what brings you here?

44:37.480 --> 44:38.880
You work so hard,

44:39.400 --> 44:41.280
and I wanted to see your office.

44:41.960 --> 44:44.160
Come with me.
I'll introduce you to everyone.

44:44.960 --> 44:46.080
First, let's eat something.

44:46.640 --> 44:47.920
I'm famished.

44:49.080 --> 44:50.160
Shall we go to the canteen?

44:51.760 --> 44:53.200
Okay. Come with me.

44:53.760 --> 44:56.200
- I'm working on a new design.
- Hmm.

44:56.360 --> 44:57.520
I'll show you after breakfast.

44:57.600 --> 44:58.640
Sure, sir.

44:59.960 --> 45:02.960
- That's Tai!
- You could have called me.

45:03.080 --> 45:04.480
I'm already here now.

45:07.280 --> 45:08.400
Is this the reason?

45:09.160 --> 45:10.240
- Come on.
- Mom, you lied.

45:10.280 --> 45:11.680
At the very least, meet him.
Come on.

45:11.760 --> 45:13.800
Do I come to work to meet suitors?

45:13.840 --> 45:16.400
Come on, my dear.
He's already here. He's truly nice.

45:17.240 --> 45:19.560
Come on. Come with me.

45:22.760 --> 45:25.400
Ms. Megha, right?

45:25.720 --> 45:26.720
Yes.

45:27.200 --> 45:28.120
Sashi!

45:29.840 --> 45:31.360
- Sashi.
- Sudha.

45:34.440 --> 45:37.080
Ah! It's a nice little place.

45:39.000 --> 45:41.480
What happened? You stopped eating.

45:43.200 --> 45:44.280
Do you like Megha?

45:45.280 --> 45:48.360
So, Ms. Megha,
will you both have tea or coffee?

45:48.640 --> 45:49.480
Coffee.

45:49.840 --> 45:51.040
- Thank you, Anna.
- Oh!

45:51.240 --> 45:52.720
Somebody's famous here.

45:54.360 --> 45:56.440
He speaks such fluent English,
doesn't he?

45:56.880 --> 45:59.400
Gaurav, a doctor can be dealt with

45:59.920 --> 46:01.400
only by another doctor.

46:01.960 --> 46:03.080
Similarly,

46:04.280 --> 46:05.840
only a Titanian can handle

46:06.800 --> 46:08.880
another Titanian.

46:10.640 --> 46:11.440
What do you think?

46:11.480 --> 46:13.920
I'm an aeronautical engineer.

46:14.120 --> 46:16.080
- An engineer for aeroplanes.
- Right.

46:16.600 --> 46:20.680
I've studied at UC Berkeley,
California.

46:22.320 --> 46:24.520
Once again, pardon my Hindi,

46:24.720 --> 46:27.920
but you must be
very proud of yourself.

46:28.760 --> 46:30.000
You work for the Tatas,

46:30.040 --> 46:32.680
and a girl at that.

46:33.760 --> 46:34.720
Amazing!

46:35.400 --> 46:36.360
Admirable.

46:38.600 --> 46:39.640
Mom, I...

46:40.320 --> 46:41.320
Megha. Megha...

46:41.880 --> 46:43.000
Mom,

46:43.320 --> 46:45.560
he's exactly the same!

46:45.600 --> 46:47.440
You keep bringing
similar suitors every time.

46:47.560 --> 46:48.920
Who introduces you to such boys?

46:48.920 --> 46:50.160
He's complimenting you.

46:50.200 --> 46:52.320
Give me your
marriage bureau's number.

46:52.320 --> 46:55.400
Uh... Um, Ms. Megha, please wait.

46:55.600 --> 46:57.800
I think you're offended.

46:58.120 --> 46:59.680
I've brought you something.

47:02.000 --> 47:04.960
A watch from your company, for you.

47:05.800 --> 47:06.760
Please.

47:10.960 --> 47:12.880
Thank you for buying it.

47:16.160 --> 47:17.560
Where did you buy it?

47:18.800 --> 47:20.680
Um, Bombay...

47:21.240 --> 47:23.080
I've forgotten
the name of the place.

47:23.720 --> 47:25.800
It's Nariman Point.

47:33.360 --> 47:34.200
What happened?

47:34.240 --> 47:35.320
- Wait a minute, Mom.
- Megha.

47:35.560 --> 47:36.720
- Megha!
- Ms. Megha, what's the matter?

47:36.800 --> 47:38.240
Please check if it's genuine.

47:38.280 --> 47:39.840
I'm sure it must be a first copy.

47:39.880 --> 47:41.960
Ms. Megha, it's original.
I've bought it from the store.

47:42.000 --> 47:43.840
Please sit quietly
and drink your coffee.

47:43.880 --> 47:45.560
Don't you dare get up
until we are back!

47:45.760 --> 47:46.840
We need to have it
checked in the workshop.

47:46.920 --> 47:47.840
Its genuineness
can't be verified here.

47:48.040 --> 47:50.040
Okay. Anna, don't let him go.

47:51.440 --> 47:52.520
What are they saying?

47:52.560 --> 47:54.560
- Is she mad?
- She will be back.

48:05.280 --> 48:06.360
It's original.

48:12.640 --> 48:13.680
All right.

48:14.520 --> 48:16.400
My friend, tell us the truth.

48:16.400 --> 48:18.000
Where did you buy the watch?

48:18.040 --> 48:19.520
My brother, I'm telling the truth.

48:19.560 --> 48:21.400
I bought it at Nariman Point.

48:21.560 --> 48:22.720
- Pardon me!
- Uh.

48:22.960 --> 48:24.160
Nariman Point!

48:24.240 --> 48:25.640
He's saying "Nariman Point".

48:25.720 --> 48:26.520
Yes!

48:26.560 --> 48:28.320
Why would he lie?

48:28.360 --> 48:30.000
Aunt, you're too naive.

48:30.760 --> 48:32.360
- Nariman Point?
- Yes!

48:32.440 --> 48:33.640
I bought it from your store.

48:33.680 --> 48:36.000
We don't have a store
at Nariman Point, you stupid!

48:36.880 --> 48:38.560
Will you tell us the truth now?

48:38.960 --> 48:40.680
- Or else...
- Um...

48:42.040 --> 48:43.520
I bought it on the black market.

48:47.480 --> 48:50.080
'Titan! Titan!
It's the latest model. Titan!'

48:50.120 --> 48:53.560
Titan! Titan! Titan!
It's the latest model. Titan!

48:54.480 --> 48:55.600
Titan?

48:59.480 --> 49:02.480
We've ended up
exactly where we started.

49:03.400 --> 49:04.440
Come on.

49:05.000 --> 49:07.000
Titan! Titan! Titan!

49:07.040 --> 49:08.720
It's the latest model. Titan!

49:08.800 --> 49:10.120
Will the police arrive on time?

49:10.200 --> 49:11.200
Yes, they will.

49:11.400 --> 49:14.280
Titan! I've got the latest model.
Titan!

49:15.600 --> 49:17.600
I can't bear to see Titan
on the black market.

49:17.880 --> 49:20.080
I feel like smacking him right away.

49:21.600 --> 49:23.000
Titan! Titan! Titan!

49:23.960 --> 49:24.800
Oi!

49:24.840 --> 49:27.080
- Oi! Stop! Stop!
- Where are you going?

49:27.120 --> 49:28.120
Wait a minute!

49:28.160 --> 49:29.960
- Come on!
- Please hear me out, sir.

49:30.000 --> 49:31.880
What did I do, sir?

49:32.240 --> 49:33.480
At least hear me out, sir.

49:33.800 --> 49:35.000
This is not done.

49:37.920 --> 49:39.800
- Sir.
- Yes?

49:40.680 --> 49:41.960
Hello, Titan Brothers!

49:42.040 --> 49:44.560
We want to speak to Jaggu.

49:45.280 --> 49:46.720
- [in Marathi] Please bring Jaggu.
- Okay, sir.

49:49.600 --> 49:50.480
- Tea?
- No.

49:50.560 --> 49:51.480
Yes, thank you.

49:52.680 --> 49:54.160
Come on! Come with me!

49:54.200 --> 49:55.960
- Sir, why are you pushing me?
- Sir!

49:56.120 --> 49:57.040
I'm walking, right?

49:57.080 --> 50:00.400
Listen! All the watches are genuine.

50:00.800 --> 50:02.160
How did you get them?

50:03.000 --> 50:05.200
Tell us honestly.
Did you steal them?

50:06.360 --> 50:07.520
Do I look like a thief?

50:08.800 --> 50:10.840
- Uh...
- I'm a businessman.

50:12.480 --> 50:13.720
An honest one.

50:14.760 --> 50:17.200
I bought all your watches at MRP.

50:17.320 --> 50:20.080
Hang on. Do you mean you bought
the watches at a high price

50:20.320 --> 50:22.040
and were selling them
at a lower one?

50:26.600 --> 50:28.400
You won't understand, sir.

50:33.320 --> 50:34.720
It's a business secret.

50:36.320 --> 50:38.480
Let's talk
businessman to businessman.

50:39.400 --> 50:40.600
Let me give you a tip.

50:40.920 --> 50:41.880
Oi!

50:42.120 --> 50:43.400
Will you really give them a tip?

50:43.760 --> 50:45.040
- Oi!
- Uh, hang on.

50:45.120 --> 50:46.000
Wait a minute!

50:46.000 --> 50:47.800
Why do you threaten me
at the drop of a hat?

50:47.840 --> 50:49.120
Please continue.

50:49.160 --> 50:50.920
- We were simply talking.
- Please go on, sir.

50:54.520 --> 50:56.760
- You've made watches
for the whole of India. - Hmm!

50:57.120 --> 50:59.040
But your watch

50:59.120 --> 51:00.600
has divided the country.

51:02.680 --> 51:04.120
How?

51:05.000 --> 51:07.800
If you check your rates
from Kashmir to Kanyakumari,

51:07.840 --> 51:09.720
your problem will be solved.

51:19.000 --> 51:21.240
Please get straight to the point.

51:21.760 --> 51:24.520
If I solve all the problems,

51:24.680 --> 51:26.240
who ought to be Titan's chairman?

51:27.760 --> 51:29.120
If you want to make me one,

51:29.240 --> 51:30.040
please go ahead!

51:31.600 --> 51:34.440
Sir, I can only tell you
this much for free.

51:34.600 --> 51:35.640
Thank you, sir.

51:35.960 --> 51:36.960
Thank you.

51:39.920 --> 51:40.880
Sir.

51:41.880 --> 51:43.280
Please grant him bail

51:43.600 --> 51:45.280
and don't press charges against him.

51:47.960 --> 51:48.880
Thank you!

51:50.840 --> 51:53.200
Zee, please tell me
what you've understood.

51:53.200 --> 51:54.880
No discussion, only demonstration.

51:55.880 --> 51:56.800
Zee!

52:02.160 --> 52:04.440
Sir, please get
the bail papers ready.
